                <div class="aboutDesc">
                    <div class="GuideHeading text-start pt-1">
                        As a beginner in diamond purchasing, let us start with the 4 Cs of Diamonds:
                    </div>
                    <ul class="m-0 pt-2">
                        <li><strong>Carat:</strong> Refers to weight measurement, influencing the physical appearance of the diamond.</li>
                        <li><strong>Cut:</strong> Affects sparkle and brilliance; easy to find “Excellent” or "Very Good” ratings.</li>
                        <li><strong>Clarity:</strong> Refers to any blemishes; diamonds with few or no inclusions are rare and thus cost more.</li>
                        <li><strong>Color:</strong> is distinguished in the scales ranging from D for colorless to Z for light yellow or brown diamonds.</li>
                    </ul>
                    <div class="GuideHeading text-start mt-4">
                        <strong>Importance of Diamond Certification</strong><br>
                        Every purchase of a diamond should come with papers issued by agencies such as the GIA or IGI. Each of these documents is grading and explains the quality factors.
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
